<p>GDP growth: 2.9% GDP: $161bn (PPP: $140bn) Inflation: 2.5% Population: 4.5m GDP per head: $35,880 (PPP: $31,240)</p>

<p>The ruling National Party was poised to win a second term in late-2011 elections, and may even secure an overall majority, unprecedented under current voting rules. Policy will continue to focus on fiscal stimulus as the country recovers from the Christchurch earthquakes. Discussions will progress with Australia on tightening economic ties, in line with the eventual creation of a single market.</p>

